<refentry id="get_page_stats">

  <refentryinfo>
    <date>$Date$</date>
    <releaseinfo>$Id$</releaseinfo>
  </refentryinfo>
  
  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>get_page_stats</refentrytitle>
    <manvolnum>3</manvolnum>
    <refmiscinfo>i-scream</refmiscinfo>
  </refmeta>
  
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>get_page_stats</refname>
    <refname>get_page_stats_diff</refname>
    <refpurpose>get paging statistics</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
    
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <funcsynopsis>
      <funcsynopsisinfo>#include &lt;statgrab.h&gt;</funcsynopsisinfo>
      <funcprototype>
        <funcdef>page_stat_t *<function>get_page_stats</function></funcdef>
        <void/>
      </funcprototype>
      <funcprototype>
        <funcdef>page_stat_t *<function>get_page_stats_diff</function></funcdef>
        <void/>
      </funcprototype>
    </funcsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
    
  <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
      <function>get_page_stats</function> and
      <function>get_page_stats_diff</function> both return a pointer to
      a static buffer of type <structname>page_stat_t</structname>.
    </para>
    <para>
      <function>get_page_stats</function> will return the number of
      pages the system has paged in and out since bootup.
      <function>get_page_stats_diff</function> will return the
      difference since last time it was called.  If it has not been
      called before, it will return
      <function>get_page_stats</function>.
    </para>
  </refsect1>
  
  <refsect1>
    <title>Return Values</title>

    <programlisting>
typedef struct{
        long long pages_pagein;
        long long pages_pageout;
        time_t systime;
}page_stat_t;
    </programlisting>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <structfield>pages_pagein</structfield>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            The number of pages swapped into memory.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <structfield>pages_pageout</structfield>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            The number of pages swapped out of memory (to swap).
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <structfield>systime</structfield>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            The time period over which <parameter>pages_pagein</parameter>
            and <parameter>pages_pageout</parameter> were transferred.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Bugs</title>
    <para>
      Solaris doesn't seem to report accurately. It reports the number
      of pages swapped into memory, not necessarily from swap. This
      feature isn't deemed entirely reliable.
    </para>
  </refsect1>

